- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper deals with multi-cloud applications, which involve distributed computing across multiple cloud providers. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes a new cloud modelling language and evaluates it through an experimental case study, which falls under the scope of software engineering. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): While the paper does not focus on data structures and algorithms, it does involve the selection of services based on specific service level objectives, which could potentially involve algorithmic approaches. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper proposes a new cloud modelling language and generates deployment code appropriate to the selected services, which falls under the scope of programming languages.
